02:27.730 --> 02:30.732
(Militaristic bugles calling)

02:30.775 --> 02:32.375
♪ ♪

02:40.618 --> 02:43.620
(Indistinct chattering)

02:49.752 --> 02:51.712
(Houston): Gentlemen, let's be clear.

02:52.054 --> 02:55.378
I would choose death before betrayal.

02:55.408 --> 02:58.034
But there is no deceit in death.

02:58.077 --> 03:00.453
Betrayal is the willful slaughter of trust.

03:00.496 --> 03:01.997
(Sherman): Sir, we saw the field...

03:02.039 --> 03:04.833
Your orders were not to engage.

03:04.875 --> 03:08.795
Your insubordination
could have cost us dearly.

03:08.838 --> 03:10.297
As of this moment,

03:10.339 --> 03:12.674
you are now reassigned to second infantry.

03:12.717 --> 03:15.427
- Sir...
- Now, get out of my sight.

03:20.658 --> 03:23.608
Cavalry now belongs to Lamar.

03:23.638 --> 03:25.245
Any objections?

03:25.287 --> 03:27.580
We've bloodied them, Sam.

03:27.623 --> 03:30.834
Perhaps we could regroup
for a counterattack.

03:30.876 --> 03:32.799
General, they're on the defensive.

03:32.829 --> 03:35.372
(Houston): I require
trust from my officers.

03:37.083 --> 03:38.792
(Houston): Towards the Sisters here.

03:38.835 --> 03:41.461
Take out the main barricade
and several points beyond.

03:41.504 --> 03:44.005
Line of infantry 1,000 yards wide.

03:44.048 --> 03:46.466
First Regiment here.

03:46.509 --> 03:49.010
Baker's rifles here.

03:49.053 --> 03:50.512
Sherman's regiment on the flank.

03:50.555 --> 03:52.889
(Baker): Well, I vote we receive an attack.

03:52.932 --> 03:54.558
(Houston): It's not up for a vote, Mosley.

03:54.600 --> 03:56.309
Besides,

03:56.352 --> 03:58.145
that's exactly what Santa
Anna thinks we'll do.

03:58.187 --> 03:59.813
Now, you might reconsider.

03:59.856 --> 04:01.648
We ought not to leave
the security of the woods.

04:01.691 --> 04:03.233
(Hockley): Where are the war dogs now?

04:03.276 --> 04:04.568
(Houston): Colonel Lamar,

04:04.610 --> 04:06.361
I want your cavalry on the right.

04:06.404 --> 04:09.823
Colonel Seguin and his
Tejanos will man the rearguard.

04:09.866 --> 04:11.158
(Seguin): No. Unacceptable.

04:11.200 --> 04:12.784
Understand, Juan, the courage

04:12.827 --> 04:15.203
of you and your men is
not in question here.

04:15.246 --> 04:18.579
There is such a deep-rooted
hatred towards Mexicans

04:18.608 --> 04:20.166
that I fear your men may have to duck

04:20.209 --> 04:21.750
more than Santanista bullets.

04:21.793 --> 04:24.004
The killing may become indiscriminate.

04:24.046 --> 04:26.256
The blood of our comrades

04:26.299 --> 04:29.718
has earned us a place
alongside you, General.

04:29.760 --> 04:33.190
My company insists on a frontline attack,

04:33.220 --> 04:35.265
come what may.

04:38.071 --> 04:40.520
(Houston): We'll need a way
to distinguish your Tejanos

04:40.563 --> 04:42.105
from Mexican soldiers.

04:42.688 --> 04:43.940
We'll wear...

04:43.983 --> 04:45.233
goose feathers

04:45.276 --> 04:46.693
as long as we can sink our teeth

04:46.736 --> 04:49.196
into Santa Anna's neck.

04:49.238 --> 04:51.448
I may have something else.

04:57.592 --> 04:59.498
Let's use these instead.

05:05.546 --> 05:10.634
(Birds chirping)

05:10.676 --> 05:12.269
(Coughs)

05:12.473 --> 05:16.422
_

05:20.102 --> 05:21.269
(Karnes): Goll dang.

05:21.312 --> 05:23.438
General Cos.

05:23.481 --> 05:24.981
Deaf. Deaf!

05:25.024 --> 05:26.650
Mexican reinforcements.

05:28.277 --> 05:29.736
Best tell Houston.

05:29.779 --> 05:32.781
(Soldiers chattering indistinctly)

05:37.568 --> 05:39.436
(Smith): They must've
been marching all night.

05:39.466 --> 05:40.674
(Karnes): They got to be tuckered.

05:40.704 --> 05:42.030
Best get before they see us.

05:42.060 --> 05:43.414
Yep.

05:44.927 --> 05:46.052
- Houston!
- Fuego!

05:46.095 --> 05:47.095
(Gunshot)

05:47.137 --> 05:48.840
(Yelps) They see us.

05:48.870 --> 05:50.306
Run!

06:01.485 --> 06:03.862
Excuse me, Señor Presidente.

06:03.904 --> 06:05.822
General Cos' troops are all present

06:05.865 --> 06:07.073
and accounted for.

06:07.116 --> 06:08.408
But exhausted from a long march.

06:08.450 --> 06:09.673
They've been up all night.

06:09.703 --> 06:11.327
So have I.

06:11.370 --> 06:13.246
Your Excellency,

06:13.289 --> 06:14.430
we should attack now.

06:14.460 --> 06:15.531
No.

06:15.561 --> 06:17.750
Houston wants us to attack

06:17.793 --> 06:19.555
so he can cut us down

06:19.585 --> 06:21.588
from the cover of those trees.

06:21.630 --> 06:23.756
So we'll wait until
Filisola and Urrea arrive?

06:23.799 --> 06:25.758
Yes, with overwhelming number,

06:25.801 --> 06:27.093
we can surround them.

06:27.136 --> 06:28.411
See?

06:28.441 --> 06:31.764
Houston will have nowhere to run.

06:31.807 --> 06:34.267
Feed the men in shifts and let them rest.

06:34.310 --> 06:35.643
Yes, sir.

06:39.064 --> 06:40.982
Houston's skirmish yesterday

06:41.025 --> 06:42.817
made no tactical sense.

06:45.112 --> 06:46.446
I don't like it.

06:48.657 --> 06:50.658
(Smith): General, we take that bridge,

06:50.701 --> 06:52.201
you won't have to worry about

06:52.244 --> 06:55.330
Santa Anna's reinforcements no more.

06:55.372 --> 06:58.124
You'll be all by your lonesome.

06:58.167 --> 06:59.667
You know I can't afford

06:59.710 --> 07:01.461
to spare you even one extra man.

07:03.505 --> 07:05.089
Forgive me, but destroying that bridge

07:05.132 --> 07:06.799
will cut off our retreat as well.

07:06.842 --> 07:08.176
(Baker): That's a good point.

07:12.723 --> 07:14.974
Then we'd better not lose.

07:25.421 --> 07:27.654
Position a crack squadron of dragoons

07:27.696 --> 07:31.115
to protect Vince's Bridge at all costs.

07:31.158 --> 07:32.649
It's our lifeline.

07:32.679 --> 07:35.244
(Almonte): Would it not be
better to abandon this position

07:35.287 --> 07:37.121
until we can rejoin all our armies

07:37.164 --> 07:38.790
and then pursue Houston on the offensive?

07:38.832 --> 07:40.020
Why?

07:40.050 --> 07:41.634
We have him!

07:41.677 --> 07:43.803
Here and now.

07:43.846 --> 07:47.682
Let his men sweat it out
while our soldiers rest.

07:49.018 --> 07:50.310
(Almonte): Yes, sir.

08:06.869 --> 08:09.913
What can I do to comfort you, Antonio?

08:24.572 --> 08:27.347
Knowles, get your slack ass up.

08:27.389 --> 08:29.349
(Water splashes)
Morning, sweet pea.

08:30.768 --> 08:31.935
Princess is up.

08:31.977 --> 08:33.394
- Lazy old bitty.
- Come on, now.

08:33.437 --> 08:34.854
Saddled up your horse for you.

08:34.897 --> 08:36.523
(Beans): Come on out. There she is.

08:36.565 --> 08:38.399
- Come on, sweet pea.
- Aww, looking pretty.

08:38.442 --> 08:39.859
(Gator): Hey, girl.

08:39.902 --> 08:41.861
(Smith): All right. That's enough.

08:41.904 --> 08:43.363
It's time.

08:43.405 --> 08:45.740
Knowles, mount up.

08:47.868 --> 08:50.119
I don't know what's ailing you, son,

08:50.162 --> 08:51.621
but whatever it is,

08:51.664 --> 08:54.290
you leave it here at camp.

08:54.333 --> 08:55.583
Kick up!

09:37.559 --> 09:39.051
(Martial bugle music)

09:39.081 --> 09:41.004
(Hockley): The general
is not to be disturbed.

09:41.046 --> 09:42.553
Come no further.

09:42.583 --> 09:43.764
(Baker): What's he doing? Sleeping?

09:43.807 --> 09:45.516
(Hockley): Step away. Step away.

09:45.559 --> 09:46.893
(Sherman): He's awake for 56 days straight;

09:46.935 --> 09:48.519
Now he sleeps?

09:48.562 --> 09:50.146
(Lamar): If he truly wanted to attack,

09:50.189 --> 09:51.564
it should've been at first light.

09:51.607 --> 09:52.899
The weather has been fickle.

09:52.941 --> 09:55.067
It's in our favor now.

09:55.110 --> 09:58.779
(Horses galloping)

09:58.822 --> 10:00.573
Who the hell is this?

10:00.616 --> 10:01.949
(Rusk): Lorca.

10:01.992 --> 10:04.660
(Horse neighs distantly)

10:05.913 --> 10:07.622
Where's General Houston?

10:07.664 --> 10:09.040
(Lamar): State your business.

10:09.082 --> 10:10.875
Saith Jehovah, "Raise your sword

10:10.918 --> 10:12.960
"with abandon and outrage

10:13.003 --> 10:15.046
till the rivers run
red with heathen blood."

10:16.248 --> 10:17.798
Amen.

10:19.301 --> 10:21.093
If you've come to bear arms with us,

10:21.136 --> 10:23.346
then I'll assign you to
Colonel Lamar's cavalry.

10:23.388 --> 10:24.764
I'll be assigned no man.

10:24.806 --> 10:26.307
Be clear on that.

10:28.018 --> 10:31.229
But we'll kill Mexicans alongside you

10:31.271 --> 10:34.920
till every brown breathing
bastard lies dead.

10:34.950 --> 10:37.109
Fair enough.

10:37.152 --> 10:39.445
When I'm ready to attack,
I'll give you a sign.

10:39.488 --> 10:40.947
Watch for it.

10:42.491 --> 10:45.159
"Vengeance is mine," saith the Lord.

10:49.706 --> 10:52.250
Sam, you can't trust that loco.

10:52.292 --> 10:56.066
This day, I'd ally with the devil himself.

10:56.096 --> 10:59.006
I think you just did.

11:18.142 --> 11:20.486
(Horse nickers)

11:21.743 --> 11:23.164
Oh.

11:25.668 --> 11:28.202
(Knowles humming)

11:28.232 --> 11:29.910
(Yelps)

11:30.781 --> 11:32.411
Tsk.

11:32.441 --> 11:33.650
(Quietly): Mind the horses.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.068
All right. All right. All right.

11:50.467 --> 11:52.010
- Knowles, damn it.
- Listen ti me.

11:52.052 --> 11:53.261
Ain't you supposed to be with the horses?

11:53.303 --> 11:54.595
I know. Just listen.

11:54.625 --> 11:56.514
I was wondering, if we blow up the bridge,

11:56.557 --> 11:59.350
how are we supposed to get back across it?

12:01.437 --> 12:02.812
We don't.

12:05.733 --> 12:08.735
(Water sloshing)

12:14.274 --> 12:15.687
You hear that?

12:15.717 --> 12:17.009
Something's in the marsh.

12:17.052 --> 12:17.884
(Water sloshing)

12:17.914 --> 12:20.576
(Man): Halt! Hands in the air!

12:20.606 --> 12:22.618
Stop right there, or I'll shoot!

12:22.648 --> 12:24.310
- (Gunshots)
- Identify yourself!

12:24.340 --> 12:25.668
- We said stop!
- It's me!

12:25.711 --> 12:27.799
It's me, Manuel Flores.

12:27.829 --> 12:30.044
Cease fire! He's one of us.

12:30.074 --> 12:31.791
Manuel, what news?

12:35.245 --> 12:37.497
Santa Anna's army is resting.

12:37.539 --> 12:38.998
His forces are tired.

12:39.402 --> 12:42.271
Emily West says it's time to attack.

12:42.301 --> 12:43.836
More reinforcements are coming.

12:43.879 --> 12:45.505
And Miss West herself?

12:48.250 --> 12:51.010
She said, "Tell General Houston

12:51.040 --> 12:52.587
"it was right to wait,

12:52.630 --> 12:54.297
but attack now."

12:54.340 --> 12:55.757
Very well.

12:55.799 --> 12:57.050
Sir.

12:59.310 --> 13:01.158
(Martial bugle music)

13:01.188 --> 13:02.788
_

13:21.501 --> 13:23.061
(Gator whispers): Easy.

13:27.873 --> 13:30.845
- (Both grunt)
- (Loud thud)

13:33.892 --> 13:37.131
(Martial bugle music)

13:37.174 --> 13:40.718
♪ ♪

13:41.061 --> 13:44.605
(Houston): You were born
to live as free men.

13:44.648 --> 13:47.233
One man took that freedom from you.

13:47.276 --> 13:52.108
One man sent your sons and
brothers to unmarked graves,

13:52.138 --> 13:56.492
your women and children
left homeless and afraid,

13:56.535 --> 13:58.962
burnt your farmlands,

13:58.992 --> 14:01.381
reduced your cherished
homesteads to ashes...

14:01.423 --> 14:03.115
one man, a tyrant,

14:03.145 --> 14:05.051
Santa Anna.

14:07.549 --> 14:09.556
Today...

14:09.843 --> 14:12.250
today we avenge our dead.

14:12.292 --> 14:14.961
We honor our loved ones.

14:15.490 --> 14:17.672
Today we are one.

14:17.714 --> 14:21.914
We are all sons of Texas.

14:21.944 --> 14:23.611
We give Texas our allegiance.

14:23.654 --> 14:26.563
We give Texas our lives.

14:27.576 --> 14:29.742
In the name of Texas,

14:30.106 --> 14:33.580
ready your weapons and
unsheathe your swords,

14:33.622 --> 14:35.790
and follow me to victory!

14:35.833 --> 14:38.835
(All cheer)

14:44.401 --> 14:45.825
They're retreating.

14:45.867 --> 14:47.535
So it seems.

14:48.159 --> 14:50.667
(Portilla): The cowards.

14:53.186 --> 14:57.044
(Martial bugle music)

14:57.087 --> 14:59.338
♪ ♪

14:59.381 --> 15:02.833
(Distant shouting in Spanish)

15:10.100 --> 15:13.102
(Footsteps)

15:23.447 --> 15:26.407
(Steady drumbeat)

15:26.450 --> 15:30.369
♪ ♪

15:30.412 --> 15:31.912
(Whispering): Good. Easy. Good.

15:31.955 --> 15:33.497
Come on. Keep it coming. Keep it coming.

15:33.540 --> 15:34.999
(Grunts)

15:37.313 --> 15:39.613
Go on. Go on. We'll string the fuse.

15:41.157 --> 15:44.117
(Martial bugle music)

15:44.160 --> 15:45.760
♪ ♪

16:01.010 --> 16:04.012
(Distant bugle music)

16:04.054 --> 16:05.654
♪ ♪

16:14.523 --> 16:15.523
That's the last one.

16:15.566 --> 16:17.275
Go on. I'll fire it up.

16:17.318 --> 16:19.694
Let's see. Let's see. Let's see.

16:19.737 --> 16:22.697
(Martial bugle music)

16:22.740 --> 16:24.340
♪ ♪

16:29.413 --> 16:30.872
(West screams, glass shatters)

16:31.215 --> 16:33.215
(West gasping)

16:52.444 --> 16:54.709
(Houston): Tell 'em to play that
song, <i>Come To The Bower.</i>

16:54.739 --> 16:57.323
Let me hear it.

16:57.365 --> 17:00.284
(Man whistling jaunty melody)

17:00.327 --> 17:01.702
♪ ♪

17:01.745 --> 17:04.788
(Jaunty drumbeat joins in)

17:04.830 --> 17:06.290
♪ ♪

17:06.333 --> 17:09.292
(Others join in whistling melody)

17:09.336 --> 17:10.935
♪ ♪

17:29.439 --> 17:30.898
(All grunting)

17:30.940 --> 17:33.942
(Martial bugle music)

17:33.985 --> 17:35.585
♪ ♪

17:50.794 --> 17:53.796
(Fuse hissing)

17:59.836 --> 18:00.753
Capitan!

18:00.796 --> 18:04.704
(Speaking Spanish)

18:04.734 --> 18:08.594
(Martial bugle music)

18:08.637 --> 18:11.013
(Fuse hissing)

18:13.016 --> 18:16.435
(Soldier speaking Spanish)

18:16.478 --> 18:17.561
(Gunshot)

18:17.604 --> 18:19.105
(Horse neighs)

18:19.147 --> 18:20.689
(Soldier speaking Spanish)

18:20.732 --> 18:22.108
(Screams)

18:22.150 --> 18:24.110
(Martial bugle music)

18:24.152 --> 18:27.996
(Soldiers speaking Spanish)

18:28.026 --> 18:29.573
(Gunshot)

18:29.616 --> 18:32.952
(Horse neighs)

18:32.994 --> 18:35.287
(Gunshot)

18:35.330 --> 18:36.288
(Gunshot)

18:36.331 --> 18:37.289
(Yelps)

18:37.332 --> 18:40.126
(Gunshots)

18:40.168 --> 18:42.294
(Soldiers shouting)

18:42.337 --> 18:44.233
(Gunshot)

18:47.008 --> 18:48.134
(Gunshot)

18:48.176 --> 18:50.932
(Explosion)

18:55.016 --> 18:58.549
(Explosion)

19:01.189 --> 19:04.194
(Explosion)

19:08.071 --> 19:09.530
(Fuse hissing)

19:09.573 --> 19:14.233
(Explosion)

19:22.919 --> 19:24.420
(Houston): Trail arms forward.

19:24.463 --> 19:26.130
Quietly, men.

19:26.173 --> 19:28.340
Keep it quiet.

20:33.281 --> 20:34.406
Fire cannon.

20:34.449 --> 20:35.908
(Hockley): Fire!

20:35.951 --> 20:38.285
(Fuse hissing, cannons boom)

20:38.328 --> 20:40.287
Remember the Alamo!

20:40.330 --> 20:42.248
(Soldiers cheering)

20:42.290 --> 20:44.815
(Soldier): Remember the Alamo!

20:54.469 --> 20:55.970
Follow me!

20:56.012 --> 20:57.263
Go!

20:57.305 --> 20:58.973
(Man shrieking)

20:59.015 --> 21:00.266
(Cannon booms)

21:00.308 --> 21:02.268
(Explosion, soldiers scream)

21:02.310 --> 21:04.645
Remember the Alamo!

21:06.982 --> 21:08.399
Charge!

21:08.441 --> 21:10.526
Remember Goliad!

21:14.406 --> 21:15.739
(Gunshot)

21:19.035 --> 21:22.037
(Distant gunfire)

21:25.667 --> 21:28.711
(Men shouting and screaming)

21:32.549 --> 21:35.301
(Soldier): Remember the Alamo!

21:35.343 --> 21:40.472
(Metallic clanging)

21:40.515 --> 21:43.309
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

21:43.351 --> 21:45.978
(West): Antonio!

21:46.021 --> 21:48.897
I have waited to see

21:48.940 --> 21:50.649
the look of defeat in your eyes.

21:53.194 --> 21:56.196
You killed my brother at the Alamo.

21:57.741 --> 22:01.535
- (Sobs)
- You killed Jupiter!

22:01.578 --> 22:03.120
(Gunshot, West screams)

22:03.163 --> 22:04.288
(Horse neighs)

22:04.331 --> 22:06.290
(Sobs)

22:10.670 --> 22:12.463
Hold the line!

22:15.050 --> 22:17.009
Attention!

22:17.052 --> 22:18.344
Attention!

22:19.721 --> 22:21.513
Hold ranks!

22:21.556 --> 22:22.848
(Yells)

22:22.891 --> 22:25.476
(Almonte): Form a line here!

22:25.518 --> 22:27.102
And fire at will!

22:29.397 --> 22:30.689
Follow me!

22:30.732 --> 22:32.191
(Soldier): Follow!

22:32.233 --> 22:35.235
(Soldiers cheering)

22:48.500 --> 22:53.179
No retreat! No retreat!

22:53.209 --> 22:55.381
Stand and fight!

22:55.423 --> 22:57.430
Go now! Go back!

22:57.460 --> 22:59.007
Go back!

22:59.382 --> 23:01.158
Go back!

23:01.188 --> 23:02.563
Back!

23:02.606 --> 23:04.356
(Horse neighs)

23:04.399 --> 23:06.025
Go!

23:10.071 --> 23:13.240
(Water splashing)

23:13.283 --> 23:15.117
(Man screams, grunts)

23:15.160 --> 23:18.162
(Water splashing)

23:27.297 --> 23:29.507
(Screaming)

23:29.549 --> 23:32.706
(Coughs, gasping)

23:32.736 --> 23:35.530
(Soldiers screaming)

23:35.572 --> 23:37.878
- No, no, no, no, no...
- (Grunts)

23:37.908 --> 23:38.908
(Soldier): Whoo-hoo!

23:38.951 --> 23:40.498
Whoo!

23:41.075 --> 23:43.011
Ride up, boys!

23:43.041 --> 23:45.021
Spread out!

23:45.051 --> 23:47.166
Whoo!

23:47.209 --> 23:50.169
(Soldiers grunting, screaming)

23:59.454 --> 24:01.580
(Gunshot)

24:01.623 --> 24:03.972
(Gunshot)

24:04.002 --> 24:05.084
Hiyah!

24:05.126 --> 24:06.655
That's it. I'm out of here.

24:06.685 --> 24:08.087
Kit!

24:08.129 --> 24:09.588
(Groaning)

24:09.631 --> 24:11.298
Come on.

24:14.111 --> 24:16.821
(Grunts)

24:16.863 --> 24:18.114
Come on, Kit.

24:18.156 --> 24:19.448
(Kit groans)

24:19.491 --> 24:23.411
Sit down right there, Kit. Get down.

24:23.453 --> 24:25.162
(Groans)

24:25.205 --> 24:27.853
Son of a bitch!

24:29.334 --> 24:30.793
Get, damn it!

24:30.836 --> 24:32.391
Take this.

24:34.656 --> 24:36.560
I'm coming back for you.

24:45.458 --> 24:47.793
Hey! Hey, get off him.

24:47.836 --> 24:49.419
Get off.

24:49.462 --> 24:52.464
(Both grunting, smacking)

25:04.936 --> 25:06.520
(Smacks, man groans)

25:10.091 --> 25:11.667
(Gunshot)

25:18.741 --> 25:20.117
(Growls)

25:20.159 --> 25:21.493
Come on!

25:33.715 --> 25:35.883
(Gunshot)

25:42.348 --> 25:45.392
(Anderson whooping)

25:48.980 --> 25:50.606
Mighty white of you, Flores.

25:50.648 --> 25:53.692
(Screaming)

25:53.735 --> 25:55.611
(Both screaming)

25:55.653 --> 25:56.591
(Screaming)

25:56.621 --> 25:58.580
Fight on, men! Follow me!

25:58.623 --> 25:59.709
(Man grunts)

25:59.739 --> 26:01.505
Hiyah!

26:03.253 --> 26:04.753
(Soldier): Remember Goliad!

26:04.796 --> 26:07.589
(Gasping)

26:07.632 --> 26:10.107
Remember the Alamo!

26:11.745 --> 26:13.329
Arm the cannon!

26:13.371 --> 26:15.255
Move!

26:15.285 --> 26:16.203
That's Houston.

26:16.233 --> 26:17.650
Turn the cannon, quickly!

26:17.692 --> 26:18.984
(Houston): Fight on, men!

26:19.826 --> 26:21.046
Yah!

26:22.071 --> 26:23.238
Fire!

26:23.281 --> 26:24.948
(Fuse hisses, cannon booms)

26:24.991 --> 26:26.992
(Explosion)

26:30.228 --> 26:31.480
Yah!

26:31.523 --> 26:34.275
(Grunting)

26:37.195 --> 26:39.363
Houston!

26:39.775 --> 26:42.050
Take my horse!

26:42.080 --> 26:44.419
Rally your men.

26:50.950 --> 26:52.960
Yah! Yah!

26:56.662 --> 26:58.306
(Gunshot)

27:06.799 --> 27:08.208
(Gunshot)

27:09.452 --> 27:13.254
(Both grunting and smacking)

27:23.115 --> 27:26.935
(Soldier): Mexicans! Remember the Alamo!

27:28.414 --> 27:31.238
(Grunts)

27:31.268 --> 27:35.639
(Coughing)

27:36.402 --> 27:37.927
Go.

27:43.617 --> 27:45.149
(Man grunting and smacking)

27:45.179 --> 27:47.056
(Screams)

27:47.414 --> 27:49.227
(Gunshot)

27:53.271 --> 27:54.730
(Screams)

27:54.773 --> 27:57.775
(Both grunting)

28:02.718 --> 28:04.406
(Karnes grunts, bones snap)

28:04.449 --> 28:06.033
(Gasps)

28:06.076 --> 28:07.159
Captain Karnes.

28:07.202 --> 28:08.494
Colby.

28:08.524 --> 28:12.414
I'm out of shot.

28:14.362 --> 28:16.091
Stay put.

28:27.196 --> 28:28.989
Surround him!

28:29.031 --> 28:32.196
(Gunfire, swords clanging)

28:32.226 --> 28:33.681
To hell with this.

28:33.711 --> 28:35.379
Come on. Yah!

28:35.421 --> 28:36.860
(Almonte): That's their war secretary!

28:36.890 --> 28:39.006
Surround him!

28:39.036 --> 28:42.724
(Knowles shouting)

28:42.754 --> 28:44.963
(Rusk): That boy saved my life.

28:45.006 --> 28:46.845
Damnedest thing I ever seen.

28:48.455 --> 28:49.801
Rusk!

28:49.844 --> 28:51.386
(Soldier): Remember the Alamo!

28:53.431 --> 28:54.640
Hiyah!

28:54.682 --> 28:57.976
(Grunting)

28:58.019 --> 28:59.770
Juan! You're one of us.

28:59.812 --> 29:00.979
I am a Tejano!

29:01.022 --> 29:02.898
(Grunts)

29:11.014 --> 29:13.092
I am a Tejano.

29:13.134 --> 29:16.428
(Bugle sounding)

29:16.471 --> 29:19.431
(All grunting and smacking)

29:26.648 --> 29:29.483
I'll find Finisola!

29:29.526 --> 29:31.235
You head west to Urrea!

29:46.293 --> 29:48.961
(Man screaming)

29:49.004 --> 29:50.212
(Gunshot)

29:50.255 --> 29:51.463
(Houston grunts)

29:51.506 --> 29:52.506
(Houston groaning)

29:52.549 --> 29:54.300
(Both grunt, swords clang)

30:00.098 --> 30:03.563
(Lorca): If Jesus Christ himself
came down from heaven today

30:04.021 --> 30:06.178
and ordered me to stop killing heathens,

30:06.221 --> 30:07.679
I would not do it!

30:07.722 --> 30:10.182
I would not do it!

30:10.512 --> 30:11.817
(Rusk): Sam!

30:11.859 --> 30:13.110
Tom!

30:15.863 --> 30:17.795
It's just a scratch.

30:18.716 --> 30:20.410
The enemy's been routed.

30:20.440 --> 30:22.127
We have to stop the killing.

30:22.157 --> 30:23.512
Get the men under control.

30:23.554 --> 30:26.723
- Cease fire! Cease fire!
- Cease fire!

30:26.766 --> 30:28.517
Cease fire!

30:28.559 --> 30:31.478
(Martial bugle music)

30:31.521 --> 30:33.121
♪ ♪

30:42.156 --> 30:45.784
(Soldier): Boy, turn around!

30:45.827 --> 30:47.285
(Gunshots)

30:47.328 --> 30:50.747
We don't take any prisoners, soldier.

30:50.790 --> 30:53.792
(Soldiers shouting, cheering distantly)

31:03.364 --> 31:06.179
(Soldiers shouting, gunfire)

31:11.844 --> 31:13.478
(Thuds, coughs)

31:13.521 --> 31:15.022
(Soldier): Cease fire!

31:15.064 --> 31:17.190
Cease fire!

31:17.233 --> 31:18.605
(Soldier): Cease fire!

31:18.635 --> 31:21.283
(Smith coughing)

31:28.893 --> 31:32.509
(Gunfire)

31:32.539 --> 31:34.515
- Mind your fire.
- Cease fire!

31:34.545 --> 31:35.786
Cease fire.

31:35.816 --> 31:37.519
They're surrendering.

31:37.549 --> 31:41.634
Cease fire. Cease fire.

31:44.619 --> 31:47.746
(Gunshots)

31:50.457 --> 31:54.933
(Speaking Spanish)

31:55.516 --> 31:57.109
We surrender!

31:57.139 --> 31:58.473
- No surrender.
- Stop this.

31:58.516 --> 32:00.271
- We surrender.
- We surrender.

32:00.301 --> 32:02.294
Remember Goliad? Remember Fannin?

32:02.324 --> 32:04.512
(Gunshot)

32:04.555 --> 32:09.065
Anderson, take these prisoners to...

32:12.766 --> 32:16.274
(Gunfire)

32:21.710 --> 32:25.063
(Almonte): Your orders
are to take prisoners.

32:25.093 --> 32:28.553
The general's orders are to take prisoners.

32:28.596 --> 32:32.891
(Man): We'll take them
just like the Mexicans did.

32:32.934 --> 32:34.559
- Who is it?
- Give them room!

32:34.602 --> 32:36.144
Coming through!

32:36.537 --> 32:37.895
I thought we won.

32:37.938 --> 32:39.336
(Soldier): Those are prisoners, General.

32:39.366 --> 32:41.708
(Rusk): We did win, Sam.

32:46.339 --> 32:47.464
(Grunts)

32:47.506 --> 32:49.216
(Seguin): General Houston!

32:49.358 --> 32:52.777
General, Texas is ours.

32:52.820 --> 32:54.612
(Sherman): An astounding victory, General.

32:54.855 --> 32:56.314
(Houston): What's your report?

32:56.344 --> 32:58.650
Around 700 Mexicans killed.

32:58.692 --> 32:59.583
At least that many prisoners.

32:59.613 --> 33:00.985
700?

33:01.228 --> 33:02.143
What about our men?

33:02.173 --> 33:04.502
Only 9 dead and 33 wounded, sir.

33:04.532 --> 33:05.823
(Rusk): 34...

33:05.866 --> 33:07.405
counting you.

33:07.435 --> 33:09.872
And Deaf is unaccounted for.

33:09.902 --> 33:11.187
(Houston): Deaf?

33:11.217 --> 33:13.565
Well, rally the Rangers.

33:14.007 --> 33:14.999
Find him.

33:15.029 --> 33:16.668
Yes, sir.

33:16.710 --> 33:18.432
(Houston): Has Santa Anna been captured?

33:18.736 --> 33:20.484
We are hunting him, sir.

33:20.514 --> 33:22.814
He must be taken alive. You hear me?

33:24.426 --> 33:26.844
Without him, there's no victory.

33:26.887 --> 33:29.472
We've won nothing.

33:29.515 --> 33:30.890
(Groans)

33:40.519 --> 33:43.315
(Lamar): Keep searching, men!

33:48.576 --> 33:50.352
(Man): Down here!

33:51.843 --> 33:53.996
Over here!

33:55.013 --> 33:57.125
This way!

34:18.897 --> 34:21.899
(Water rushing)

34:24.945 --> 34:28.820
(Rustling)

34:28.850 --> 34:30.266
Mexicano!

34:30.309 --> 34:31.976
Mexicano. Mexicano!

34:32.020 --> 34:33.478
Benito?

34:34.123 --> 34:35.396
Benito,

34:35.438 --> 34:38.315
you are one of the keepers
of my champion birds.

34:38.659 --> 34:39.543
Presidente?

34:39.572 --> 34:41.953
- Si.
- Presidente.

34:41.995 --> 34:46.706
My friends are all dead.

34:50.243 --> 34:52.685
We lost.

34:52.958 --> 34:56.025
We lost a lot of friends today.

35:01.907 --> 35:03.283
(Man): Put him down over there.

35:06.996 --> 35:08.621
I thought you'd be hanging curtains

35:08.664 --> 35:12.750
and darning your fiancé's socks by now.

35:12.793 --> 35:14.511
I'm not going anywhere yet.

35:14.541 --> 35:16.643
Drink this.

35:17.631 --> 35:18.923
(Man): I need to clean this.

35:18.966 --> 35:20.967
Get me some more water.

35:21.323 --> 35:22.951
Do you love him?

35:24.079 --> 35:25.329
Gavin's a goodhearted man.

35:25.372 --> 35:26.831
He's decent.

35:26.874 --> 35:29.166
Daddy loved him, promised
me to him years ago.

35:29.209 --> 35:32.086
Answer my damn question.

35:36.758 --> 35:38.050
(Groaning)

35:38.093 --> 35:39.677
(Man): Just get him some laudanum.

35:39.720 --> 35:42.021
(Panting)

35:42.051 --> 35:46.480
You don't want what I got to give, no way.

35:46.510 --> 35:48.382
The next bullet that comes
my way might be my last.

35:48.412 --> 35:50.242
Don't say such things.

35:50.272 --> 35:51.539
You know, my whole life,

35:51.582 --> 35:54.084
people have been telling
me what's good for me.

35:54.126 --> 35:56.962
(Man): Back over when you've got a minute.

35:57.753 --> 36:00.253
You'd be a damn fool not to go with him.

36:02.426 --> 36:05.178
No, you're the fool, Kit Acklin.

36:09.745 --> 36:12.085
(Crunching, man screaming)

36:12.115 --> 36:14.462
(Houston): Where am I?

36:14.905 --> 36:16.844
Did they cut my leg off?

36:16.874 --> 36:19.417
(Doc Ewing): No, but
your ankle was shattered.

36:19.459 --> 36:20.981
If sepsis sets in,

36:21.011 --> 36:24.305
you will die a slow, miserable death.

36:24.348 --> 36:25.640
Any word from Emily?

36:25.683 --> 36:26.606
(Doc Ewing): No.

36:26.636 --> 36:28.976
We got to get you to New Orleans.

36:29.019 --> 36:31.479
If not, should you fall unconscious,

36:31.522 --> 36:33.815
I will have that leg off.

36:33.857 --> 36:37.527
I'll take my chances in New Orleans.

36:40.039 --> 36:41.360
Emily.

36:41.390 --> 36:44.392
(Distant gunfire)

36:57.740 --> 37:00.784
(Coughing)

37:06.466 --> 37:09.334
(Indistinct shouting)

37:09.377 --> 37:11.378
(Shushing)

37:15.216 --> 37:18.510
(Distant shouting)

37:18.552 --> 37:21.596
(Distant cannonfire)

37:25.393 --> 37:28.353
(Whimpering)

37:35.190 --> 37:37.320
Am I dying, padre?

37:42.953 --> 37:43.952
Si.

37:54.215 --> 37:56.215
(Sobbing)

38:03.764 --> 38:05.140
(Karnes): Deaf.

38:06.067 --> 38:07.456
Deaf!

38:07.897 --> 38:10.061
(Flames crackling)

38:12.765 --> 38:15.680
(Distant banging)

38:29.534 --> 38:33.042
(Loud banging)

38:35.461 --> 38:37.255
(Knowles): Oh-ho!

38:38.674 --> 38:41.342
Well, chop my legs and call me Shorty.

38:41.385 --> 38:44.095
Vern! Vern, ain't this swank?

38:44.688 --> 38:45.876
Ain't this swank?

38:45.906 --> 38:46.998
Close this thing.

38:47.028 --> 38:48.396
Hey, take a look at this.

38:48.426 --> 38:49.592
Take a look at this.

38:49.635 --> 38:51.344
(Breathes noisily): One second.

38:51.946 --> 38:54.153
General Santa Annabella herself.

38:54.183 --> 38:56.199
Ooh, well, hello there.

38:56.229 --> 38:58.447
Hello. Hello, there.

38:58.477 --> 39:00.311
The spoils of war, son.

39:00.354 --> 39:01.842
We grab what we can hold,

39:01.872 --> 39:03.564
and we cut out of here tonight.

39:03.607 --> 39:05.066
Yes, sir. Whoa, whoa, no.

39:05.108 --> 39:06.359
I don't know.

39:06.401 --> 39:07.610
Vern, Vern, hey, Vern.

39:07.653 --> 39:09.491
You got to understand.

39:09.521 --> 39:11.147
I'm a hero now.

39:11.190 --> 39:14.288
I saved the war secretary's life.

39:14.694 --> 39:18.529
I heard you tripped
over a bunch of Mexicans.

39:18.572 --> 39:19.530
It...

39:19.573 --> 39:20.508
(Thudding and grunting)

39:20.538 --> 39:21.999
Ha!

39:26.080 --> 39:27.664
Eureka.

39:30.234 --> 39:32.193
Holy shit.

39:43.914 --> 39:45.206
(Gun cocks)

39:47.209 --> 39:48.710
(Colby Pitt): Surrender, Mexican,

39:48.752 --> 39:51.754
or I'll kill you deader than last Tuesday.

39:51.797 --> 39:55.550
On your knees. On your knees.

39:55.593 --> 39:57.927
Are you alone?

39:58.470 --> 39:59.887
Maybe.

40:05.703 --> 40:07.608
Hands up.

40:07.638 --> 40:09.097
Hands up!

40:18.106 --> 40:19.566
God damn. We can't get it all now.

40:19.608 --> 40:22.193
Got to come back before we head out.

40:22.236 --> 40:24.362
- (Metallic clattering)
- (Gasps)

40:24.755 --> 40:27.548
Well, goodness gracious.

40:27.591 --> 40:29.472
What is this?

40:30.844 --> 40:34.472
It's the mother lode...
Santa Anna's treasure.

40:34.515 --> 40:36.474
You snakes weren't gonna tell me about it?

40:36.517 --> 40:37.684
Well, why should we?

40:37.726 --> 40:39.548
We found it.

40:39.578 --> 40:42.163
Lucky for me,

40:42.193 --> 40:43.848
so did I.

40:43.891 --> 40:47.323
(Karnes): That there must
be El Presidente's tent.

40:48.050 --> 40:49.583
(Elwood): Cover this shit up. That's right.

40:49.613 --> 40:51.739
- All right.
- Cover it up.

40:51.782 --> 40:54.855
- All right.
- That's right.

41:00.290 --> 41:02.896
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo-whee!

41:02.926 --> 41:05.303
Awful highfalutin.

41:05.345 --> 41:07.555
(Laughs)

41:07.598 --> 41:10.187
Looks like this place done been looted.

41:10.217 --> 41:13.052
We was just picking up
a few souvenirs, man.

41:13.095 --> 41:14.825
Spoils of war and such.

41:14.855 --> 41:17.277
Well, you know that looting

41:17.307 --> 41:21.611
could get you court-martialed and shot.

41:21.641 --> 41:24.897
- (Laughs nervously)
- What, you mean...

41:24.940 --> 41:29.861
even for a token or two
for our loyalty to Texas?

41:29.903 --> 41:31.785
Listen up.

41:31.815 --> 41:34.171
All this belongs to the Texas government.

41:34.441 --> 41:36.588
So if you don't mind, I'll take...

41:36.618 --> 41:39.537
- Captain, you all right?
- Son of a bitch.

41:40.736 --> 41:42.707
(Quietly): Damn.

41:42.750 --> 41:46.807
Oh, lookee here.

41:47.248 --> 41:49.303
Would you look at that?

41:49.333 --> 41:52.592
Santa Anna must've buried that, right?

41:52.634 --> 41:54.594
Must have.

41:54.636 --> 41:55.970
All of it.

42:01.656 --> 42:05.980
(Loud thud)

42:06.023 --> 42:08.900
(Metallic clinking and thud)

42:08.942 --> 42:10.902
(Quietly): Damn.

42:10.944 --> 42:13.738
(Indistinct chatter)

42:13.781 --> 42:16.783
(Scattered cheering)

42:25.834 --> 42:27.877
(Man): Yeah!

42:27.920 --> 42:30.922
(All cheering)

42:34.343 --> 42:35.593
How about that?

42:35.636 --> 42:38.721
(Man): Vive, El Presidente!

42:38.764 --> 42:40.681
(Man): Yeah!

42:40.724 --> 42:43.356
(Doc Ewing): It's a tincture of opium, Sam,

42:43.386 --> 42:46.103
for the pain.

42:46.146 --> 42:49.023
Quart of warm whiskey
would work just as well.

42:52.453 --> 42:55.413
General, you've got to see this.

42:55.456 --> 42:56.619
He needs to rest.

42:56.649 --> 42:58.149
I need fresh air.

42:58.192 --> 43:00.527
Fetch my clothes.

43:00.569 --> 43:03.279
Haul me up, Tom.

43:03.322 --> 43:06.324
(Hockley): By my count,
we have over 20,000 pieces

43:06.367 --> 43:07.825
of silver and gold...

43:07.868 --> 43:10.495
all of Santa Anna's
personal valuables, sir.

43:10.538 --> 43:13.206
(Seguin): General, we must give
these to the people of Tejas.

43:13.249 --> 43:15.500
(Rusk): Gentlemen, there is
no discussion on this matter.

43:15.543 --> 43:17.168
Funds seized from the enemy

43:17.211 --> 43:20.672
belong to the newly liberated Republic.

43:20.714 --> 43:22.173
(Man): Another group going in.

43:22.216 --> 43:24.676
(Rusk): It all goes to Texas.

43:28.722 --> 43:31.849
Karnes, that soldier there.

43:31.892 --> 43:33.101
Bring him to me.

43:33.143 --> 43:34.519
(Karnes): Sir.

43:34.562 --> 43:36.521
Flores, fetch Colonel Almonte.

43:36.564 --> 43:38.898
Yes, sir.

43:38.928 --> 43:40.191
(Man): Move!

43:40.234 --> 43:41.979
(Indistinct chatter)

43:42.009 --> 43:45.109
- (Flores): Colonel Almonte...
- (Karnes): Come on.

43:58.736 --> 44:00.695
So you're a private.

44:01.285 --> 44:04.537
Si, señor.

44:05.217 --> 44:07.598
Colonel Almonte,

44:07.628 --> 44:10.588
why do your men salute him?

44:10.631 --> 44:11.835
Regretfully,

44:11.865 --> 44:13.987
I do not know all my soldiers, sir.

44:14.017 --> 44:15.889
That's too bad.

44:15.919 --> 44:17.169
Private Pitt,

44:17.897 --> 44:20.151
execute your prisoner.

44:22.418 --> 44:23.835
(Colby Pitt): Yes, sir.

44:25.337 --> 44:27.505
(Houston): No, private.

44:28.673 --> 44:30.341
Put him up against a tree

44:30.384 --> 44:32.923
so his brains don't splatter.

44:36.122 --> 44:39.642
I am Antonio Lopez de Santa Anna.

44:39.685 --> 44:40.651
Wait. He's Santa Anna?

44:40.681 --> 44:44.268
And I am Sam Houston.

44:44.298 --> 44:46.466
El Presidente, General,

44:46.736 --> 44:48.757
I cannot express

44:48.787 --> 44:52.555
how glad I am to meet you.

44:52.871 --> 44:54.604
I ask to be treated as a general should be

44:54.634 --> 44:57.168
when made a prisoner of war.

44:57.211 --> 44:58.461
Men!

44:58.504 --> 45:00.547
We captured Santa Anna!

45:00.929 --> 45:03.508
We must convene a tribunal and execute him.

45:03.551 --> 45:06.177
(Baker): Death by firing squad!

45:06.220 --> 45:09.180
(All): yeah!

45:09.223 --> 45:10.515
(All talking at once)

45:10.558 --> 45:12.058
Yeah!

45:12.101 --> 45:15.103
(All shouting)

45:16.905 --> 45:19.991
The conqueror of the Napoleon of the West

45:20.476 --> 45:23.870
can afford to be generous
to the vanquished, no?

45:23.912 --> 45:25.788
You should have remembered that, sir,

45:25.831 --> 45:27.498
at the Alamo.

45:27.541 --> 45:30.376
At the Alamo, your defenders chose to die.

45:30.419 --> 45:32.416
You offered them no alternative.

45:32.446 --> 45:34.568
- (Spits)
- Bastardo.

45:34.598 --> 45:36.307
Juan...

45:38.151 --> 45:39.819
This is war, sir,

45:39.861 --> 45:43.168
and no one here is good or bad,

45:43.693 --> 45:45.863
just winners

45:45.893 --> 45:49.473
and losers.

45:49.503 --> 45:51.898
I acted under the orders
from my government.

45:51.940 --> 45:54.191
You are yourself the government.

45:54.234 --> 45:55.776
That's damn right.

45:55.819 --> 45:58.029
(Rusk): Texas formed a
recognized government.

45:58.071 --> 45:59.697
We are not pirates.

45:59.740 --> 46:01.699
The rules of war applied.

46:01.742 --> 46:04.201
General, why are we even
talking to this murderer?

46:04.244 --> 46:05.849
He needs to swing.

46:05.879 --> 46:08.673
Firing squad, here and now!

46:08.716 --> 46:12.343
(All): Yeah!

46:12.386 --> 46:15.471
(All talking at once): Do it!

46:15.514 --> 46:16.973
- Yeah!
- (Men shouting)

46:30.994 --> 46:34.866
(Men shouting)

46:34.908 --> 46:37.156
(Houston): There'll be no firing squad.

46:37.186 --> 46:39.178
(Man): We want blood!

46:39.221 --> 46:41.868
(Houston): That cannot happen.

46:41.898 --> 46:45.309
Alive, Santa Anna is of great value to us.

46:45.502 --> 46:47.962
If we execute him,

46:48.005 --> 46:51.298
he'll just be another dead soldier.

46:51.612 --> 46:53.155
Let us take our reparations.

46:53.185 --> 46:55.194
Open his war chest.

46:55.237 --> 46:57.154
Gold to every man in my command.

46:57.197 --> 47:01.367
Equal shares for all those
who risked their lives.

47:01.409 --> 47:03.786
General Seguin, General Sherman,

47:03.829 --> 47:05.621
show the men.

47:05.664 --> 47:06.914
Divvy it up.

47:06.957 --> 47:09.834
(Sherman): Yes, sir.

47:09.876 --> 47:12.878
(All cheering)

47:33.150 --> 47:36.530
General, we're taking him.

47:36.560 --> 47:37.858
Retribution goes hand in hand

47:37.888 --> 47:39.346
with victory.

47:39.389 --> 47:41.182
Present your prisoner.

47:41.224 --> 47:43.517
I will not.

47:46.474 --> 47:48.355
All right, fine by me.

47:50.600 --> 47:52.977
We end it all now.

47:53.020 --> 47:55.980
My only reason for living

47:56.023 --> 47:57.940
is to slay him.

47:59.347 --> 48:01.736
Ride on out of here while you can.

48:01.778 --> 48:04.131
Shut your mouth, boy.

48:04.161 --> 48:05.856
Shoot me first.

48:06.575 --> 48:08.489
You don't think I will?

48:09.570 --> 48:12.599
Soldiers, ready arms!

48:36.664 --> 48:38.289
Don't fool yourself.

48:38.332 --> 48:41.471
Santa Anna will die!

48:41.501 --> 48:42.835
It's just a matter

48:42.878 --> 48:46.046
of how many of us he takes with him.

48:49.843 --> 48:52.136
You understand me?

49:55.617 --> 49:58.535
(Coughs)

50:11.425 --> 50:12.591
Charmaine.

50:12.634 --> 50:13.783
(Horse neighs)

50:13.813 --> 50:15.678
(Groans)

50:15.720 --> 50:17.876
Come here, girl.

50:17.906 --> 50:19.223
Come here.

50:19.266 --> 50:21.387
You saved me today.

50:33.672 --> 50:35.563
Oh, sweet girl.

50:37.724 --> 50:39.105
(Groans)

50:39.135 --> 50:42.976
(Horse whinnies)

50:44.111 --> 50:46.141
No.

50:50.288 --> 50:54.458
Why'd you have to go do that for?

50:54.501 --> 50:56.001
Why'd you do that?

51:18.024 --> 51:20.234
I'm so sorry.

51:22.537 --> 51:24.038
(Crying): I'm so sorry.

51:28.835 --> 51:31.337
Come on. Let's get you off that leg.

51:31.379 --> 51:33.547
Let's get you off that leg, okay?

51:50.236 --> 51:52.558
You do me a favor.

52:00.205 --> 52:02.743
You do me a favor.

52:02.786 --> 52:05.788
You wait for me. You hear?

52:05.831 --> 52:08.754
You wait for me.

52:08.784 --> 52:11.535
You'll be seeing me real soon.

52:13.622 --> 52:14.872
(Gun cocks)

52:14.915 --> 52:17.541
(Exhales)

52:17.584 --> 52:18.959
(Gunshot)

52:19.002 --> 52:20.669
(Gunshot echoing)

52:20.712 --> 52:23.380
(Crying)

52:35.268 --> 52:36.602
(Snickers)

52:36.645 --> 52:39.647
(Indistinct chatter in Spanish)

52:54.788 --> 52:57.039
(Distant galloping)

52:57.082 --> 52:58.290
(Man screaming)

52:58.333 --> 53:02.044
(All speaking Spanish)

53:02.087 --> 53:03.254
(Lorca): Get every one of them!

53:03.296 --> 53:04.588
Every one of them!

53:04.631 --> 53:05.798
Hey, come on!

53:05.841 --> 53:07.133
(Gunshot, woman screams)

53:07.175 --> 53:08.467
Come on!

53:08.510 --> 53:11.053
(People shouting indistinctly)

53:14.057 --> 53:15.516
(Panting)

53:15.559 --> 53:20.271
(Gunshot)

53:20.313 --> 53:23.315
(Laughter)

53:25.068 --> 53:26.402
(Gasps)

53:29.863 --> 53:31.365
No! He's just a child.

53:31.408 --> 53:32.783
Nits make lice.

53:32.826 --> 53:35.202
We're done killing women and children!

53:35.245 --> 53:36.787
Then get out of here!

53:36.830 --> 53:38.964
I aim to kill Mexicans,
and I ain't done yet.

53:40.000 --> 53:41.292
- Go.
- All right.

53:41.334 --> 53:43.168
Just go, man. Go.

53:43.710 --> 53:45.254
Go!

53:45.297 --> 53:46.839
Come on, man.

53:50.886 --> 53:54.138
Give me the boy.

54:00.854 --> 54:02.980
(Gunshot)

54:09.196 --> 54:10.584
(Thunder rumbles)

54:10.614 --> 54:12.073
(Houston): Any word from Deaf?

54:12.115 --> 54:13.449
(Flores): No, General.

54:13.892 --> 54:15.100
And Miss West?

54:15.143 --> 54:16.727
Nothing, sir.

54:19.335 --> 54:21.268
Very well.

54:26.279 --> 54:29.281
You wanted to keep me alive, no?

54:29.324 --> 54:32.409
Once you are gone, these men will hang me.

54:34.871 --> 54:36.121
Tell me something.

54:36.164 --> 54:39.306
Your generals... will they retreat

54:39.336 --> 54:42.177
once they're informed
you've been taken hostage?

54:42.220 --> 54:43.216
No.

54:43.696 --> 54:45.781
Their orders are to engage.

54:50.711 --> 54:53.755
Then I recommend you rescind those orders.

54:55.442 --> 54:58.610
So you want Texas

54:58.653 --> 55:01.572
in exchange for my life, huh?

55:01.614 --> 55:03.073
Sounds like a trade.

55:03.116 --> 55:04.283
(Rusk): Only President Burnett

55:04.325 --> 55:06.368
can negotiate a treaty.

55:06.411 --> 55:08.245
(Houston): Well, he
can't very well negotiate

55:08.288 --> 55:10.080
if El Presidente here is dead.

55:10.123 --> 55:11.582
Now, can he?

55:16.463 --> 55:18.088
(Woman): I'll need them vials.

55:18.131 --> 55:21.091
(Indistinct chatter)

55:25.130 --> 55:26.618
Kit,

55:26.648 --> 55:28.751
are you sure you're fit to ride?

55:28.781 --> 55:30.943
Hey, now, don't fuss.

55:30.985 --> 55:32.319
In case I need tending to,

55:32.362 --> 55:35.557
Doc Ewing's coming with the General.

55:36.574 --> 55:38.367
I'll see you when I get back.

55:38.409 --> 55:39.910
I certainly hope so...

55:39.953 --> 55:42.788
if you don't get yourself killed.

56:15.738 --> 56:19.871
(Elwood whistling)

56:26.499 --> 56:29.501
(Doc Ewing): Sarah, you got
my medical bag packed up yet?

56:32.088 --> 56:34.828
I'll be seeing you.

56:35.108 --> 56:37.234
(Doc Ewing): Sarah!

56:46.327 --> 56:48.203
Where you heading to, Vern?

56:50.628 --> 56:53.083
War is over for me, Knowles.

56:53.126 --> 56:54.293
I done my duty.

56:54.335 --> 56:56.587
Had my fill of taking orders.

56:56.855 --> 56:59.047
Might head on down to Victoria.

56:59.090 --> 57:00.879
Mm.

57:00.909 --> 57:02.493
You want to know my guess?

57:02.966 --> 57:06.413
You and Gator are going after that bank.

57:06.456 --> 57:09.500
Gator's so full of bunkum,
if he told me water was wet,

57:09.542 --> 57:12.503
I'd have to poke my finger
in and feel for myself.

57:13.947 --> 57:15.781
Kit didn't trust him.

57:16.123 --> 57:17.245
You ought not to neither.

57:17.275 --> 57:18.921
Well, I ain't robbing no bank.

57:18.951 --> 57:20.457
I'm a hero now.

57:20.487 --> 57:23.155
Got a reputation to uphold.

57:27.959 --> 57:31.705
Well, if you want to ride
your hero ass along with me,

57:31.748 --> 57:33.123
you're welcome.

57:34.709 --> 57:36.788
Well...

57:38.505 --> 57:40.631
no, thank you, my friend.

57:41.381 --> 57:44.259
I reckon I'll just stay put.

57:47.610 --> 57:49.797
Good luck with that shit.

57:52.905 --> 57:55.124
Tell them boys I say adios.

57:55.154 --> 57:57.071
All right.

58:02.081 --> 58:04.429
You lily-livered weasel.

58:04.472 --> 58:05.722
How in the hell am I supposed

58:05.765 --> 58:07.504
to take this bank by myself?

58:07.534 --> 58:11.036
Well, why don't you
recruit Karnes and Anderson?

58:23.032 --> 58:26.723
(Houston): Tom, I want you
to ride on ahead to Burnett.

58:26.753 --> 58:29.546
Formalize our agreement with Santa Anna.

58:29.589 --> 58:32.153
Buckley and Seguin will
take charge of the army

58:32.183 --> 58:33.340
while I'm away.

58:33.370 --> 58:35.268
(Rusk): You get that leg healed up, Sam.

58:35.311 --> 58:36.561
Texas needs you.

58:36.591 --> 58:37.562
(Grunts)

58:37.592 --> 58:41.444
You just gonna leave me behind, is that it?

58:41.501 --> 58:44.770
Well, I'll be damned.

58:44.800 --> 58:46.438
I'd about given up on you.

58:47.805 --> 58:50.534
I had to lay Charmaine to rest.

58:52.574 --> 58:54.113
(Karnes): Partner, damn.

58:54.155 --> 58:56.073
You look like something the cat dragged in

58:56.116 --> 58:58.594
that the goat wouldn't eat.

58:58.624 --> 58:59.878
Right here.

58:59.908 --> 59:00.744
(Coughs)

59:00.787 --> 59:03.080
Let it out.

59:03.351 --> 59:05.207
Let it on out.

59:08.161 --> 59:09.551
(Houston): Private Pitt.

59:10.984 --> 59:12.214
The man that captured Santa Anna

59:12.257 --> 59:14.680
ought to make a damn good Ranger.

59:14.710 --> 59:16.456
Your first assignment:

59:16.486 --> 59:18.762
Take Captain Smith home to his wife.

59:18.805 --> 59:20.417
Yes, sir.

59:20.447 --> 59:23.309
Sorry to hear about Charmaine.

59:23.351 --> 59:26.787
(Smith): Anybody fetch me a new mount yet?

59:26.817 --> 59:28.824
(Doc Ewing): Get a wagon
and lay him down in back.

59:28.993 --> 59:31.066
You're in no condition to go, Deaf.

59:35.525 --> 59:37.948
What'd you say, Sam?

59:38.209 --> 59:40.463
You need to look me in the eye.

59:44.331 --> 59:48.042
I said you're not going.

59:48.084 --> 59:50.919
And who's gonna look after
your old crippled ass?

59:52.783 --> 59:55.495
Karnes will take command of the Rangers.

59:56.843 --> 59:58.469
Just gonna throw me away.

59:58.511 --> 01:00:00.165
Is that it?

01:00:03.731 --> 01:00:06.310
Go home, old friend.

01:00:08.005 --> 01:00:11.361
The Republic of Texas
is grateful for your service.

01:00:11.391 --> 01:00:12.911
Go on.

01:00:12.941 --> 01:00:14.017
(Doc Ewing): All right.

01:00:14.060 --> 01:00:17.354
Colby, get him in the medical tent.

01:00:17.702 --> 01:00:19.398
Got to get Houston to New Orleans

01:00:19.440 --> 01:00:23.068
and Santa Anna to his peace talks.

01:00:23.111 --> 01:00:24.736
You take care of yourself, Deaf.

01:00:25.813 --> 01:00:27.489
(Houston): Let's move out.

01:00:27.532 --> 01:00:29.491
(Smith): Sam.

01:00:29.534 --> 01:00:30.867
Sam.

01:00:30.910 --> 01:00:33.453
I'll tell you when I'm done.

01:00:38.384 --> 01:00:39.801
Yah.

01:01:04.778 --> 01:01:06.995
(Groaning)

01:01:10.781 --> 01:01:13.544
(Fly buzzing)

01:01:34.690 --> 01:01:37.317
(Doc Ewing): You just had one, Sam.

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:38.526
That's quite enough.

01:01:38.569 --> 01:01:39.861
Mmm!

01:01:47.720 --> 01:01:50.221
You think you are a man of destiny,

01:01:50.264 --> 01:01:52.140
but all I see

01:01:52.183 --> 01:01:54.184
is President Jackson's puppet.

01:01:56.228 --> 01:01:58.938
All I see is a man in a chicken coop.

01:01:59.081 --> 01:02:01.708
I am defending my people
against pirates like you,

01:02:01.750 --> 01:02:04.081
stealing our land.

01:02:04.111 --> 01:02:07.906
History will sweep you
aside with a footnote.

01:02:07.948 --> 01:02:09.491
Perhaps.

01:02:09.533 --> 01:02:10.867
Better a footnote

01:02:10.910 --> 01:02:13.453
than a whole book of abominations.

01:02:13.496 --> 01:02:15.121
(Chuckles)

01:02:15.164 --> 01:02:18.291
No difference with what
you did in San Jacinto.

01:02:18.334 --> 01:02:20.335
We are men on opposite sides,

01:02:20.377 --> 01:02:22.796
yet there is much we share.

01:02:22.838 --> 01:02:25.340
A love of our countries,

01:02:25.382 --> 01:02:29.010
a love of... other things.

01:02:29.053 --> 01:02:31.429
A remarkable woman, Miss West.

01:02:32.608 --> 01:02:34.766
An extraordinary woman,

01:02:34.809 --> 01:02:37.056
especially in bed

01:02:37.086 --> 01:02:39.129
when she's screaming with pleasure.

01:02:41.132 --> 01:02:42.632
I hear women are quite skilled

01:02:42.675 --> 01:02:45.051
at pretending that sort of thing.

01:02:45.094 --> 01:02:48.805
"Oh, Antonio, yes, yes, more.

01:02:48.848 --> 01:02:50.473
Give me more."

01:02:50.516 --> 01:02:53.184
Give him another one, Doc.

01:02:53.227 --> 01:02:56.271
He's wrestling with
what defeat tastes like.

01:03:11.446 --> 01:03:14.831
(Water splashing)

01:03:23.632 --> 01:03:26.468
Colonel Portilla's got Emily West.

01:03:26.510 --> 01:03:28.219
Wants to trade her for Santa Anna.

01:03:30.401 --> 01:03:32.223
A whore for a chief of state.

01:03:33.610 --> 01:03:36.269
Portilla is losing his mind.

01:03:42.810 --> 01:03:44.602
Give this back to him.

01:03:46.366 --> 01:03:47.891
Flores.

01:03:49.758 --> 01:03:51.050
Sir?

01:03:51.093 --> 01:03:54.053
(Speaking foreign language)

01:03:54.096 --> 01:03:55.388
Yes, sir.

01:03:55.431 --> 01:03:56.723
Anderson!

01:04:18.120 --> 01:04:19.078
- Yeah.
- Get ready.

01:04:19.121 --> 01:04:20.079
God is with us.

01:04:20.122 --> 01:04:21.310
Ha!

01:04:21.340 --> 01:04:22.716
Beads and whiskey

01:04:22.758 --> 01:04:24.342
always worked for me before.

01:04:28.931 --> 01:04:30.765
Whoa, whoa. Keep your head, mister.

01:04:30.808 --> 01:04:33.143
Else you're liable to lose
it along with your scalp.

01:04:34.603 --> 01:04:36.396
Everything's set.

01:04:36.439 --> 01:04:39.107
I need my volunteers.

01:04:39.150 --> 01:04:40.442
(Woman): Get out there, Phineas.

01:04:40.484 --> 01:04:41.501
- You be a man.
- All right.

01:04:41.531 --> 01:04:44.149
I can give you Clarence
and the other Negroes.

01:04:44.179 --> 01:04:45.258
Best if I stay back

01:04:45.288 --> 01:04:48.685
and watch over the children and womenfolk.

01:04:49.660 --> 01:04:52.370
Bigfoot, let's meander.

01:04:56.379 --> 01:04:58.548
Well, move it.

01:05:43.139 --> 01:05:44.931
(Horse whinnies in the distance)

01:05:50.212 --> 01:05:52.964
Must've hanged your president by now.

01:05:53.007 --> 01:05:54.937
When I know that's true,

01:05:54.967 --> 01:05:56.926
I'll use you for my men's amusement.

01:05:56.969 --> 01:05:59.345
And where will you go?

01:05:59.588 --> 01:06:03.132
Texas... they'll hang you for Goliad.

01:06:03.175 --> 01:06:06.983
In Mexico, they'll shoot
you for San Jacinto.

01:06:07.013 --> 01:06:08.888
- (Smacks)
- (Yelps)

01:06:22.753 --> 01:06:24.854
(Speaks Spanish)

01:06:37.584 --> 01:06:40.628
(Whooping)

01:07:03.784 --> 01:07:07.196
(Whooping)

01:07:25.916 --> 01:07:28.968
(Fuse hissing)

01:07:34.172 --> 01:07:36.184
(Explosion)

01:07:36.226 --> 01:07:39.228
- (Horses neighing)
- (Native Americans whooping)

01:07:42.107 --> 01:07:43.399
Shh.

01:07:43.442 --> 01:07:44.650
(Whooping)

01:07:44.693 --> 01:07:46.069
Now! Fire!

01:07:46.111 --> 01:07:49.113
(Gunshots, whooping, and horses neighing)

01:07:57.206 --> 01:07:59.665
Fire. Fire!

01:07:59.708 --> 01:08:02.710
(Gunshots and whooping)

01:08:22.981 --> 01:08:25.274
Fire, boys. Fire!

01:08:25.317 --> 01:08:28.319
(Whooping)

01:08:31.907 --> 01:08:33.323
(Laughs)

01:08:33.367 --> 01:08:34.951
Come here, boy. We did it!

01:08:34.993 --> 01:08:37.328
- Whoo!
- We drove them off.

01:08:37.371 --> 01:08:40.163
Everybody good over there?

01:08:40.207 --> 01:08:43.459
(All cheering): We done it!

01:08:43.502 --> 01:08:44.669
(Distant cheering)

01:08:44.711 --> 01:08:45.962
I'll be damned.

01:08:46.004 --> 01:08:47.337
It worked!

01:08:47.381 --> 01:08:48.965
Slicker than snot on a doorknob!

01:08:51.176 --> 01:08:53.094
(Woman): Blessed be the saints!

01:08:53.136 --> 01:08:54.929
Saints, hell.

01:08:54.971 --> 01:08:56.848
Thank Jack Hays.

01:08:56.890 --> 01:08:58.140
Come in.

01:08:58.183 --> 01:09:00.059
(Laughter)

01:09:00.102 --> 01:09:01.310
Come in!

01:09:01.353 --> 01:09:04.147
(Laughter)

01:09:04.189 --> 01:09:05.481
Come on in.

01:09:05.524 --> 01:09:07.567
(Laughing)

01:09:18.036 --> 01:09:21.080
- (Flesh sizzling)
- (Groaning)

01:09:24.710 --> 01:09:27.670
(Faint music)

01:09:27.712 --> 01:09:29.313
♪ ♪

01:09:43.602 --> 01:09:45.720
That music,

01:09:46.189 --> 01:09:47.279
is it for me?

01:09:47.310 --> 01:09:48.500
You're famous, Sam.

01:09:48.529 --> 01:09:51.390
Savior of Texas.

01:09:51.420 --> 01:09:52.879
You've got to stay put.

01:09:52.921 --> 01:09:55.298
You're gonna bust open your damn stitches.

01:09:55.341 --> 01:09:57.759
People want to see me.

01:09:57.801 --> 01:09:59.802
Help me.

01:09:59.845 --> 01:10:01.054
Damn it.

01:10:01.096 --> 01:10:03.931
(Houston grunting)

01:10:03.974 --> 01:10:05.641
Put your leg over here.

01:10:05.684 --> 01:10:08.770
(Houston grunting)

01:10:08.812 --> 01:10:10.271
Consarn it, Sam,

01:10:10.314 --> 01:10:12.774
you can't put any weight on that leg.

01:10:12.816 --> 01:10:14.067
That's why I'm leaning on you.

01:10:14.109 --> 01:10:17.111
(Jubilant music and cheering, faintly)

01:10:17.154 --> 01:10:20.740
♪ ♪

01:10:20.783 --> 01:10:22.075
I got him.

01:10:22.117 --> 01:10:25.036
(Jubilant music and cheering)

01:10:25.079 --> 01:10:26.692
♪ ♪

01:10:26.922 --> 01:10:28.381
Thank you.

01:10:28.424 --> 01:10:29.528
(Crowd chanting "Houston!")

01:10:29.558 --> 01:10:31.163
Thank you!

01:10:31.193 --> 01:10:33.285
Give me your hat.

01:10:33.315 --> 01:10:36.322
My hat? Why?

01:10:36.965 --> 01:10:38.132
Thank you!

01:10:38.174 --> 01:10:38.968
(Crowd cheering)

01:10:39.029 --> 01:10:40.368
Sam.

01:10:40.411 --> 01:10:42.996
(Crowd cheering)

01:10:43.560 --> 01:10:44.998
Nurse!

01:10:45.240 --> 01:10:46.866
That was my best hat.

01:10:46.909 --> 01:10:49.125
♪ ♪

01:10:58.041 --> 01:10:59.429
Be careful.

01:10:59.459 --> 01:11:01.598
(Pauline Wykoff): I need fresh air.

01:11:01.856 --> 01:11:03.767
The wound will reopen.

01:11:03.809 --> 01:11:05.393
(Exhales loudly)

01:11:10.032 --> 01:11:12.859
(Panting)

01:11:19.767 --> 01:11:22.452
What will you do when you're strong again?

01:11:22.495 --> 01:11:25.280
Go back to Tennessee?

01:11:25.310 --> 01:11:27.999
I came out with my husband and kids

01:11:28.042 --> 01:11:29.793
to find a better life.

01:11:33.506 --> 01:11:34.881
I got to stay.

01:11:40.446 --> 01:11:42.310
(Sighs)

01:11:52.912 --> 01:11:55.735
(Men coughing)

01:12:05.332 --> 01:12:09.395
Forbear, Don Antonio. Forbear.

01:12:09.425 --> 01:12:11.811
Portilla will come to save us.

01:12:13.322 --> 01:12:17.474
If I owned both hell and Texas,

01:12:17.934 --> 01:12:21.866
I would rent Texas and live in hell.

01:12:29.253 --> 01:12:30.420
(Girl): Mrs. Smith!

01:12:30.463 --> 01:12:32.589
Mrs. Smith, we got your husband!

01:12:32.631 --> 01:12:34.873
Captain Smith is here.

01:12:37.002 --> 01:12:38.294
Please, give me a hand.

01:12:38.337 --> 01:12:39.567
(Smith): We did it, darling.

01:12:39.597 --> 01:12:41.431
Texas is ours.

01:12:41.474 --> 01:12:43.058
Are you all right?

01:12:49.733 --> 01:12:52.484
Come here.

01:12:52.526 --> 01:12:55.499
Hey, hey, that's him, ain't it?

01:12:55.529 --> 01:12:57.321
- Captain Smith?
- Yes, sir.

01:12:57.364 --> 01:13:00.145
Captain Deaf Smith, fresh from San Jacinto.

01:13:00.175 --> 01:13:01.426
War is won, mostly.

01:13:03.182 --> 01:13:05.054
Splendid.

01:13:05.097 --> 01:13:06.764
We managed to miss it
in search of a trinket.

01:13:06.807 --> 01:13:09.376
Ain't a trinket.

01:13:09.606 --> 01:13:11.619
Hell, if Texas does to us
what it did to him and Samuel,

01:13:11.662 --> 01:13:15.107
we might ought to give California a shot.

01:13:22.631 --> 01:13:25.592
(Faint choral music)

01:13:25.634 --> 01:13:27.234
♪ ♪

01:13:44.723 --> 01:13:47.570
(Baby crying)

01:13:53.937 --> 01:13:55.188
(Doors clatter open)

01:13:55.230 --> 01:13:56.731
(Congregation gasps)

01:13:56.773 --> 01:13:59.775
(All murmuring)

01:14:19.554 --> 01:14:23.933
Christ washed the feet of lepers.

01:14:26.269 --> 01:14:27.490
Thank you for coming.

01:14:27.520 --> 01:14:31.779
This is a special moment
in the life of my grandson.

01:14:36.460 --> 01:14:38.656
(Baby crying)

01:15:06.155 --> 01:15:09.228
(Choir singing softly)

01:15:09.271 --> 01:15:12.857
♪ ♪

01:15:12.899 --> 01:15:14.942
(Doors creak)

01:15:14.972 --> 01:15:20.322
(Doors close heavily)

01:15:20.365 --> 01:15:23.367
(Baby crying)

01:15:40.921 --> 01:15:42.866
Salute, Louis.

01:15:44.890 --> 01:15:47.516
You remember me, mister?

01:15:47.759 --> 01:15:48.968
Yes, ma'am.

01:15:49.010 --> 01:15:52.560
Unfortunate what happened.

01:15:54.099 --> 01:15:56.938
You sold us that place
knowing the Comanches

01:15:56.968 --> 01:15:58.373
were running loose.

01:15:58.403 --> 01:15:59.662
As I recall,

01:15:59.692 --> 01:16:02.494
your husband inquired only
of the Mexican turmoil.

01:16:02.524 --> 01:16:04.404
The subject of Indians never come up.

01:16:04.434 --> 01:16:05.952
(Spits)

01:16:09.119 --> 01:16:11.148
Carts!

01:16:11.191 --> 01:16:12.566
What the hell are you doing out here?

01:16:12.596 --> 01:16:15.424
I told you to get back in there
and finish that goddamn...

01:16:15.454 --> 01:16:17.718
(Shouting indistinctly)

01:16:23.442 --> 01:16:27.173
(Doors creak open)

01:16:28.356 --> 01:16:31.576
(Footsteps)

01:16:58.747 --> 01:17:01.207
(Door creaks open)

01:17:01.249 --> 01:17:02.875
(Door creaks and shuts heavily)

01:17:13.236 --> 01:17:14.870
(Anderson): Colby.

01:17:14.913 --> 01:17:16.514
Hey!

01:17:16.544 --> 01:17:18.641
Round up men for a posse.

01:17:18.684 --> 01:17:20.313
We got a rescue mission.

01:17:20.343 --> 01:17:21.594
Where is Deaf?

01:17:21.636 --> 01:17:22.841
Over there.

01:17:22.871 --> 01:17:24.121
Show the way.

01:17:28.335 --> 01:17:30.085
(Man): Can't go with you. I'm sorry.

01:17:30.128 --> 01:17:32.213
Got my belly full of killing.

01:17:32.490 --> 01:17:34.048
I'll shoe your horses and fix your tack

01:17:34.090 --> 01:17:36.217
free of charge anytime you want.

01:17:36.259 --> 01:17:38.761
(Woman): Erastus is done rangering.

01:17:38.954 --> 01:17:41.163
Let him know peace in his final days.

01:17:41.206 --> 01:17:44.166
Yes, ma'am. Yes, ma'am.

01:17:44.209 --> 01:17:47.503
We're just here to look after
his well-being

01:17:47.545 --> 01:17:48.921
and to pay our respects.

01:17:48.964 --> 01:17:50.172
You think I don't see?

01:17:50.215 --> 01:17:52.091
There is trouble somewhere.

01:17:52.133 --> 01:17:53.425
You want men.

01:17:54.761 --> 01:17:58.347
There's been a kidnapping.

01:17:58.390 --> 01:18:00.724
Yeah, the lady who
helped us beat Santa Anna.

01:18:00.767 --> 01:18:02.977
You found Emily West?

01:18:03.019 --> 01:18:05.020
You get back in that bed.

01:18:05.063 --> 01:18:06.563
I've got to take a country leak, woman,

01:18:06.606 --> 01:18:08.691
unless you want to mop up this floor.

01:18:08.733 --> 01:18:09.984
Bueno.

01:18:16.527 --> 01:18:19.118
Deaf. This is...

01:18:19.148 --> 01:18:21.233
Captain Smith, name's Jack Hays.

01:18:21.263 --> 01:18:22.367
This here is Bigfoot Wallace.

01:18:22.397 --> 01:18:24.273
It's a real honor to meet you, sir. I...

01:18:24.316 --> 01:18:26.233
Are you the Tennessee
turned up and saved this town

01:18:26.276 --> 01:18:27.687
from the Comanches?

01:18:27.717 --> 01:18:29.039
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

01:18:30.739 --> 01:18:32.365
That was nice work.

01:18:32.407 --> 01:18:34.504
Thank you.

01:18:35.125 --> 01:18:36.837
Hey, come on.

01:18:38.090 --> 01:18:41.061
Deaf, we're... we're not here
to give you any trouble.

01:18:41.091 --> 01:18:43.967
We... we don't want
to cause a commotion.

01:18:43.997 --> 01:18:45.177
We just don't want to...

01:18:45.220 --> 01:18:46.824
Though we could use your advice.

01:18:46.854 --> 01:18:47.980
Please.

01:18:48.352 --> 01:18:50.107
Advice.

01:18:52.546 --> 01:18:54.611
Don't marry a woman that can whoop you.

01:18:54.654 --> 01:18:57.656
She'll make you piss yourself.

01:18:57.699 --> 01:18:59.365
Portilla's got her. Don't he?

01:18:59.395 --> 01:19:00.826
That's right.

01:19:00.868 --> 01:19:03.144
I think I remember seeing him ride off.

01:19:03.174 --> 01:19:06.044
I figured she was dead.

01:19:06.074 --> 01:19:07.783
Didn't tell nobody.

01:19:07.813 --> 01:19:10.786
(Coughing)

01:19:23.692 --> 01:19:25.777
I'm gonna need a new mount.

01:19:26.844 --> 01:19:28.771
(Anderson): Done.

01:19:28.813 --> 01:19:30.631
(Woman): Excuse me.

01:19:35.658 --> 01:19:37.362
Deaf, no.

01:19:37.405 --> 01:19:39.794
If you go out that door,

01:19:39.824 --> 01:19:42.021
we know you ain't coming back.

01:19:42.051 --> 01:19:45.618
Lupe, darling,

01:19:46.058 --> 01:19:49.420
I am coughing blood and farting dust.

01:19:51.377 --> 01:19:53.087
Now, I reckon I can die in that bed

01:19:53.129 --> 01:19:56.006
watching all your caterwauling,

01:19:56.049 --> 01:19:58.133
or I can die as I've tried my damnedest

01:19:58.176 --> 01:20:00.648
to live all my days:

01:20:00.678 --> 01:20:02.592
Like a man.

01:20:06.851 --> 01:20:10.540
You done real good keeping
me around this long.

01:20:11.176 --> 01:20:14.079
Can you do one more thing?

01:20:14.109 --> 01:20:17.281
You mind fetching me my clothes?

01:20:32.854 --> 01:20:35.040
Those look real good.

01:20:37.885 --> 01:20:40.438
Mind your chores,

01:20:40.676 --> 01:20:43.744
and you be a comfort to your ma, you hear?

01:20:44.180 --> 01:20:46.682
Now, when you get older, well,

01:20:47.049 --> 01:20:51.103
I'm gonna expect you
to account for yourself.

01:20:51.270 --> 01:20:54.981
Texas is gonna need a
young lady like yourself.

01:20:55.611 --> 01:20:57.781
All right?

01:20:59.333 --> 01:21:02.214
I'm mighty proud of you.

01:21:14.377 --> 01:21:17.504
There ain't words for how much I love you.

01:21:33.479 --> 01:21:35.339
(Anderson): Make way!

01:21:50.079 --> 01:21:51.288
(Knock at door)

01:21:51.331 --> 01:21:52.915
(Man): Sam.

01:21:52.957 --> 01:21:55.792
Your enemies are conspiring
against you as we speak.

01:21:55.835 --> 01:22:00.547
(Burnet): He and Houston
want to annex our Texas.

01:22:02.634 --> 01:22:06.929
If you would accept this...

01:22:06.971 --> 01:22:09.014
It must be used for good.

01:22:09.057 --> 01:22:11.266
Your land is now forfiet
as well as the collateral...

01:22:11.309 --> 01:22:13.019
You can't have Nate.

01:22:14.646 --> 01:22:16.772
What about this one?

01:22:16.814 --> 01:22:19.149
Shoo, shoo, in the kitchen.

01:22:19.192 --> 01:22:22.861
Santa Anna's whore doesn't
eat with decent folk.

01:22:22.904 --> 01:22:25.781
I very much like your house.

01:22:25.823 --> 01:22:27.159
It would suit me.

01:22:27.189 --> 01:22:29.047
They may have cleaned you up.

01:22:29.077 --> 01:22:30.665
I know you.

01:22:30.695 --> 01:22:34.156
What do we got to do to join
up with a ranger company?

01:22:34.199 --> 01:22:37.826
(Gunshots)

01:22:37.869 --> 01:22:39.536
(Whooping)

01:22:39.579 --> 01:22:41.747
(Shouts)

01:22:41.790 --> 01:22:44.145
And I suggest you finish
up your little party here

01:22:44.175 --> 01:22:45.634
and come with us and get back home

01:22:45.677 --> 01:22:47.565
and fix Texas before it's too late.

